ZHAC — Multi-component license overview
========================================

ZHAC is published as a collection of repositories, each under its own
license. Canonical license texts live in `LICENSES/`. Each submodule
carries its own authoritative `LICENSE` file.

| Submodule          | License              | SPDX              |
|--------------------|----------------------|-------------------|
| embedded-zhc       | Apache License 2.0   | Apache-2.0        |
| zhac-components    | Mixed (see below)    | per-file / per-component |
| zhac-main-core     | GNU AGPL v3 or later | AGPL-3.0-or-later |
| zhac-net-core      | GNU AGPL v3 or later | AGPL-3.0-or-later |
| www-spa            | GNU AGPL v3 or later | AGPL-3.0-or-later |

Mixed-license detail for `zhac-components`:

| Component in zhac-components      | License              |
|-----------------------------------|----------------------|
| zap_common                        | Apache-2.0           |
| metrics                           | Apache-2.0           |
| event_bus, hap_protocol,          | AGPL-3.0-or-later    |
| hap_session, hap_json,            | AGPL-3.0-or-later    |
| device_shadow, device_backend,    | AGPL-3.0-or-later    |
| zap_store, zhc_adapter            | AGPL-3.0-or-later    |

The per-component `LICENSE` file inside `zhac-components` is the
authoritative source. Individual source files carry an
`SPDX-License-Identifier:` header.

Third-party code vendored into any submodule is listed in that
submodule's `NOTICE` file; the aggregate is in `zhac-platform/NOTICE`.

Contributions are accepted only under the Contributor License
Agreement in `CLA.md`. The CLA grants the maintainer broad rights —
including the right to relicense — which allows ZHAC to be offered
under multiple licenses (open-source + a commercial / cloud option)
without renegotiating with every past contributor.

Copyright © 2025–2026 Evgenij Cjura and project contributors.

"ZHAC" and associated names, logos, and marks are not covered by any
of the licenses above. See `NOTICE` for the trademark statement.
